";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"hosting services\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Multi-vendor\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Performance\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:7;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://wedevs.com/?p=87854\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:541:\"<p>We at weDevs, the provider of best multivendor marketplace Dokan, have been trying to provide the most convenient solutions from&#8230; </p>\n<p class=\"read-more\"><a class=\"btns\" href=\"https://wedevs.com/87854/speed-up-multivendor-store-with-cloudways/\">Continue reading &#8594;</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wedevs.com/87854/speed-up-multivendor-store-with-cloudways/\">How I Increased the Speed of my Multivendor Store with Cloudways</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wedevs.com\">weDevs</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"Mainul Kabir Aion\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20540:\"<p>We at weDevs, the provider of best multivendor marketplace Dokan, have been trying to provide the most convenient solutions from beginning. Thus, we have been trying to focus on different aspects besides our own plugin for helping our users.</p>\n<p>While you are doing business with your multivendor marketplace, speed is one of the most important elements that can get you success. Researchers have found out that website owners have only <a href=\"https://www.tributemedia.com/blog/you-have-7-seconds-what-a-visitor-should-know-about-your-website-within-moments\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">7 seconds to grab</a> attention of their visitors. While that is addressed, Page-speed is also <a href=\"https://www.searchenginejournal.com/2017s-four-important-ranking-factors-according-seo-industry-studies/184619/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">one of the ranking factors</a>. Websites on desktops with a decent internet connection should load in <strong>less than 3 seconds</strong>, while mobile sites are to be loaded in <strong>less than 2 seconds</strong>. So, it’s definitely a catch to speed up your Multivendor store.</p>\n<p>Thus, we decided to highlight the most important step for a speedy multivendor store using <strong>Dokan</strong> and <strong>Cloudways</strong>.</p>\n<h2>Dig a Lot Before Choosing Your Hosting Provider</h2>\n<p>There are a number of hosting providers that claims to be the fastest in the industry until you test them. You can become disappointed with their performance. So, we have done a bit of a research on different types of hosting and how they work out for you.</p>\n<h3>Shared Hosting</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Shared-Hosting.jpg\"><img data-attachment-id=\"87855\" data-permalink=\"https://wedevs.com/87854/speed-up-multivendor-store-with-cloudways/shared-hosting/\" data-orig-file=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Shared-Hosting.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"760,470\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Shared Hosting\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Shared-Hosting-300x186.jpg\" data-large-file=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Shared-Hosting.jpg\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-87855\" src=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Shared-Hosting.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"760\" height=\"470\" srcset=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Shared-Hosting.jpg 760w, https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Shared-Hosting-300x186.jpg 300w, https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Shared-Hosting-600x371.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" /></a></p>\n<p>We found out that most WordPress marketplace users are using Shared Hosting. No doubt, they are very powerful servers, but the only con is, they share resources with other sites on the same server. This can increase the load time on the server and ultimately, it will affect your website performance too, irrespective of the amount of optimization you have done.</p>\n<p>Same goes with the security. If an attacker manages to get into any of the hosted site on server, he can access all of the sites hosted on that server. That might be <strong>YOURS</strong>!</p>\n<h3>VPS Hosting</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/VPS-Hosting.jpg\"><img data-attachment-id=\"87856\" data-permalink=\"https://wedevs.com/87854/speed-up-multivendor-store-with-cloudways/vps-hosting/\" data-orig-file=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/VPS-Hosting.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"760,470\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"VPS Hosting\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/VPS-Hosting-300x186.jpg\" data-large-file=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/VPS-Hosting.jpg\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-87856\" src=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/VPS-Hosting.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"760\" height=\"470\" srcset=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/VPS-Hosting.jpg 760w, https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/VPS-Hosting-300x186.jpg 300w, https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/VPS-Hosting-600x371.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Then we have VPS (Virtual Private Server), in which only you are the owner of the server. The only con for VPS is that it can undergo hardware failure in case something happens to your server. You will ultimately lose every ounce of data on it.</p>\n<h3>Cloud Hosting</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Cloud-Hosting.jpg\"><img data-attachment-id=\"87857\" data-permalink=\"https://wedevs.com/87854/speed-up-multivendor-store-with-cloudways/cloud-hosting/\" data-orig-file=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Cloud-Hosting.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"760,470\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Cloud Hosting\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Cloud-Hosting-300x186.jpg\" data-large-file=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Cloud-Hosting.jpg\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-87857\" src=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Cloud-Hosting.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"760\" height=\"470\" srcset=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Cloud-Hosting.jpg 760w, https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Cloud-Hosting-300x186.jpg 300w, https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Cloud-Hosting-600x371.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" /></a></p>\n<p>To overcome cons of Shared and VPS hosting, “<strong>Cloud Hosting</strong>” is a rapidly growing terminology that has gained significant fame within the digital world. Due to it’s reliability, security and performance, it is one of the widely accepted hosting service around. So what really happens in Cloud hosting? The hosting resources for each website is replicated on every Cloud server in the form of a cluster.</p>\n<p>For example, if one cloud server has maximum traffic already, then it automatically routes the query for the specific site to the idle cloud server in the cluster. This dramatically provides more reliability and increases the overall performance of your WordPress website.</p>\n<h3>What We Think Would Improve Your Store\'s Speed</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Our-Recommendation.jpg\"><img data-attachment-id=\"87858\" data-permalink=\"https://wedevs.com/87854/speed-up-multivendor-store-with-cloudways/our-recommendation/\" data-orig-file=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Our-Recommendation.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"760,470\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Our Recommendation\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Our-Recommendation-300x186.jpg\" data-large-file=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Our-Recommendation.jpg\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-87858\" src=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Our-Recommendation.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"760\" height=\"470\" srcset=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Our-Recommendation.jpg 760w, https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Our-Recommendation-300x186.jpg 300w, https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Our-Recommendation-600x371.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" /></a></p>\n<p>If you consider the above facts, it would be better to go with a cloud infrastructure provider such as Google Compute Engine, Amazon Web Services, DigitalOcean or KYUP &#8211; a container based infrastructure provider in which your server size can automatically be increased or decreased on traffic spikes at particular thresholds. But, you will need to hire a high paying dedicated SysAdmin to setup the server on any infrastructure provider. If you can not bear the cost, there are other solutions like Managed WordPress Hosting which takes care of all kind of server stuff and your server will be managed by them.</p>\n<h2>How Cloudways can Help You to Speed Up Your Dokan Store</h2>\n<p>We observed, one of the fastest growing Managed WordPress hosting is <a href=\"https://www.cloudways.com/en/?id=91316\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Cloudways</a>, that set up a deal with top 5 cloud infrastructure providers including <strong>Google Computer Engine, DigitalOCean, Amazon Web Services</strong> etc. to provide maximum up-time, security and best performance.</p>\n<p>They are like the bridge between you and your server. All server side hassles are easily handled by their expert team. In case you encounter any problem, there is always a live chat box available to assist you at any time.</p>\n<p>We decided to test Dokan on Cloudways and share benchmarks that can help you make a decision for a speedy multivendor store on WordPress.</p>\n<h2>Install WordPress on Cloud</h2>\n<p>Installing the WordPress is pretty straight forward as it takes only a few clicks to install on Cloudways. We assume, you have already installed <strong>WooCommerce</strong> and <strong>Dokan</strong> plugin on your WordPress.</p>\n<h3>Testing Environment</h3>\n<p>To conduct tests, we have created a testing environment on clean WordPress installation.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>DigitalOcean 1GB Server (New York)</li>\n<li>PHP 7 &amp; MySQL 5.6</li>\n<li>Tested from California (Pingdom)</li>\n<li>WordPress 4.7.x</li>\n<li>WooCommerce 3.0</li>\n<li>Dokan</li>\n<li>Grand-Popo (WooCommerce Theme)</li>\n<li>500 Products</li>\n<li><strong>Varnish Disabled</strong></li>\n<li><strong>No caching plugin</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>And here are the results.</p>\n<h3>Time To First Byte (TTFB)</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/time-to-first-byte.jpg\"><img data-attachment-id=\"87859\" data-permalink=\"https://wedevs.com/87854/speed-up-multivendor-store-with-cloudways/time-to-first-byte/\" data-orig-file=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/time-to-first-byte.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"1544,446\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"time to first byte\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/time-to-first-byte-300x87.jpg\" data-large-file=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/time-to-first-byte-1024x296.jpg\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-87859\" src=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/time-to-first-byte.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1544\" height=\"446\" srcset=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/time-to-first-byte.jpg 1544w, https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/time-to-first-byte-300x87.jpg 300w, https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/time-to-first-byte-768x222.jpg 768w, https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/time-to-first-byte-1024x296.jpg 1024w, https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/time-to-first-byte-600x173.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1544px) 100vw, 1544px\" /></a></p>\n<h3>Stable Performance</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/stable-performance.jpg\"><img data-attachment-id=\"87860\" data-permalink=\"https://wedevs.com/87854/speed-up-multivendor-store-with-cloudways/stable-performance/\" data-orig-file=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/stable-performance.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"1538,439\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title